The Idols judge has been going around spreading love and charity wherever he goes and this week decided to give meals to the homeless.Taking to Instagram, Somizi explained that he was inspired by a recent promotion by McDonalds and noticed the large amount of homeless people in a park in Johannesburg. That inspired me to come in here today to buy burgers, like a full meal, at McDonalds... I decided out of my own pocket to buy between 150 to 500 meals, he said in a video.He encouraged his followers to do the same by buying or giving one meal to those in need.But this is not the first time that Somizi has given back.Good tipperSomizi made a waiter's day late last year by leaving him a hefty tip.A post shared by Somizi (@somizi) on Nov 25, 2016 at 6:45am PST A post shared by Somizi (@somizi) on Nov 25, 2016 at 6:45am PSTGiving data to fansSomizi made it rain data earlier this year when he loaded up data and airtime vouchers on Instagram for his followers to use.A post shared by Somizi (@somizi) on Jan 3, 2017 at 10:30am PSTA post shared by Somizi (@somizi) on Jan 3, 2017 at 10:30am PST Making your matric dance dreams come trueThe TV personality gave away 30 of his designer suits last year to underprivileged teenage boys to wear to their matric dance, all in the spirit of Mandela Day. 